          "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/bitcoin/bitcoin/git/commits/b425a81f07068877f63fda159cdacf9dd1b4104c",
          "sha": "b425a81f07068877f63fda159cdacf9dd1b4104c",
          "html_url": "https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/commit/b425a81f07068877f63fda159cdacf9dd1b4104c"
        }
      ],
      "message": "net: fix 1970 epoch stale tx bug in private_broadcast\n\nWhen a transaction is added to the private broadcast queue via\n`try_emplace`, its node attempts vector is initialized empty.\nThe `GetStale` loop passes this empty vector to `DerivePriority`,\nwhich defaults `last_confirmed` to the Unix Epoch (0). This causes\nthe stale checker to immediately flag freshly added transactions\nas stale, resulting in redundant broadcast logs.\n\nThis commit fixes the bug by wrapping the attempts vector in a\n`TxState` struct that natively tracks `time_added`. `GetStale`\nnow checks `num_confirmed == 0` to cleanly determine if a tx\nis unconfirmed, measuring age against `time_added` instead of\n`last_confirmed`.\n\nAdditionally, this commit updates the surrounding loop to use\nuniform initialization and const-correctness, and upgrades the\ntest suite to use `BOOST_REQUIRE_EQUAL` to prevent out-of-bounds\nmemory access violations during size checks.",
      "committer": {
        "name": "Mccalabrese",
        "email": "nw.calabrese@gmail.com",
        "date": "2026-03-20T04:16:34Z"
      },
